01:44:44,519 --> 01:44:48,853
We're now down to the big game
and we await the haka of New Zealand.

1214
01:44:49,023 --> 01:44:50,752
[YELLING IN MAORl]

1215
01:45:30,731 --> 01:45:34,599
Well, that's the challenge that's laid down
by the Maoris before going into battle.

1216
01:45:42,843 --> 01:45:44,208
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1217
01:45:49,617 --> 01:45:51,847
Outside, outside!

1218
01:45:57,258 --> 01:46:00,056
ANNOUNCER 2: ... New Zealand with the best
attacking side of the tournament.

1219
01:46:17,712 --> 01:46:20,180
ANNOUNCER 1: This first 20 minutes
will be absolutely critical.

1220
01:46:20,348 --> 01:46:22,748
South Africa has the weight advantage
in the scrums...

1221
01:46:22,917 --> 01:46:25,886
... but I don't think many people have
seen a weak New Zealand scrum.

1222
01:46:26,053 --> 01:46:28,613
[MEN SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1223
01:46:36,530 --> 01:46:38,157
Put it out!

1224
01:46:40,267 --> 01:46:43,100
South Africa had it in the maul
and they should've played it.

1225
01:46:43,270 --> 01:46:46,330
Good interplay by New Zealand.
Now, here's a chance for them.

1226
01:46:51,912 --> 01:46:53,470
Engage.

1227
01:46:54,715 --> 01:46:56,205
Break.

1228
01:47:04,859 --> 01:47:06,554
Come, boys.

1229
01:47:07,428 --> 01:47:08,952
What the heck are we doing?

1230
01:47:09,130 --> 01:47:10,859
Lomu is culling us.

1231
01:47:11,032 --> 01:47:14,399
Forwards, we must start scrumming.

1232
01:47:14,568 --> 01:47:18,368
We must disrupt him at the first phase.
Can't allow Lomu to get the ball in space.

1233
01:47:18,539 --> 01:47:19,767
He's freaking killing us.

1234
01:47:19,940 --> 01:47:23,376
But listen, if Lomu gets the ball,
whoever's there...

1235
01:47:23,544 --> 01:47:25,478
...James, Joost...

1236
01:47:25,646 --> 01:47:27,978
...hit the fucking guy,
hold onto him, hold him.

1237
01:47:28,149 --> 01:47:29,980
Help will come, help will be there.

1238
01:47:30,151 --> 01:47:31,982
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1239
01:47:32,153 --> 01:47:34,383
We can see that New Zealand
were looking to try...

1240
01:47:34,555 --> 01:47:38,514
... and stretch the game to the left to Jonah
Lomu, and give him some time and space.

1241
01:47:47,068 --> 01:47:48,535
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

1242
01:48:16,397 --> 01:48:18,865
Most of the opportunities
have gone New Zealand's way.

1243
01:48:19,333 --> 01:48:21,460
Now, now, now!

1244
01:48:29,643 --> 01:48:32,271
Penalty. Carrying the ball.

1245
01:48:35,950 --> 01:48:37,440
That's the mark.

1246
01:48:37,618 --> 01:48:40,280
Captain. Posts.

1247
01:48:47,361 --> 01:48:50,091
ANNOUNCER: Kick is good.
Number 10, Andrew Mehrtens.

1248
01:48:50,364 --> 01:48:52,525
First blood to New Zealand.

1249
01:48:52,867 --> 01:48:54,994
Great all-around fly half
is Andrew Mehrtens...

1250
01:48:55,169 --> 01:48:58,195
... born here in South Africa in Durban.

1251
01:49:09,416 --> 01:49:13,546
And now Stransky gets a kick that's every
bit as important as the one that Mehrtens...

1252
01:49:22,563 --> 01:49:24,724
The kick is good.
Number 10, Joel Stransky.

1253
01:49:28,002 --> 01:49:29,902
New Zealand to restart.

1254
01:50:00,501 --> 01:50:02,833
REFEREE:
Penalty. Carrying the ball.

1255
01:50:03,003 --> 01:50:04,334
Posts.

1256
01:50:08,142 --> 01:50:10,110
Such an important kick for New Zealand.

1257
01:50:16,283 --> 01:50:20,185
The penalty kick is converted.
Andrew Mehrtens for New Zealand.

1258
01:50:20,354 --> 01:50:24,848
The score now:
New Zealand, 6, South Africa, 3.

1259
01:50:25,025 --> 01:50:27,550
It's a great kick from Mehrtens.
Thirteen minutes gone.

1260
01:50:27,728 --> 01:50:30,526
They're at 6 points to 3,
New Zealand leads South Africa.

1261
01:50:37,571 --> 01:50:39,095
MAN 1: Release the ball.
MAN 2: Come on.

1262
01:50:39,273 --> 01:50:40,797
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1263
01:50:54,355 --> 01:50:58,587
About 21 minutes gone.
Both teams, up on it, 6 points each.

1264
01:51:18,679 --> 01:51:21,773
Boks kick a goal for the lead
for the first time in the match.

1265
01:51:36,130 --> 01:51:40,362
[CROWD SINGING "OLE OLE OLE"]

1266
01:51:53,047 --> 01:51:54,480
MAN:
Last feet.

1267
01:51:54,648 --> 01:51:57,446
Stay. Stay.

1268
01:52:02,356 --> 01:52:04,153
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1269
01:52:04,325 --> 01:52:06,623
ANNOUNCER:
Successful attempt for New Zealand.

1270
01:52:08,462 --> 01:52:10,487
MAN:
Wide, wide!

1271
01:52:41,028 --> 01:52:44,828
ANNOUNCER:
Unsuccessful kick. The score remains 9-9.

1272
01:52:45,232 --> 01:52:48,224
That's the closing score, 9 points all.

1273
01:52:48,402 --> 01:52:50,962
And now there will be
a five-minute break.

1274
01:52:51,372 --> 01:52:55,365
This is the first final in the history of the
World Cup where we're having extra time.

1275
01:52:58,278 --> 01:53:00,246
Extra time.

1276
01:53:00,781 --> 01:53:03,306
So, what does this mean?

1277
01:53:03,484 --> 01:53:06,385
Extra time. Twenty minutes.

1278
01:53:07,054 --> 01:53:09,215
I don't think I can take it.

1279
01:53:09,390 --> 01:53:14,521
ANNOUNCER: lt'll be a test of great character
in these last 20 minutes of this match.

1280
01:53:15,963 --> 01:53:18,625
Who's the fittest team on this field?

1281
01:53:18,799 --> 01:53:21,859
Who's the fittest team on this field?

1282
01:53:32,513 --> 01:53:34,743
Outside, outside!

1283
01:53:41,722 --> 01:53:44,589
REFEREE:
Crouch. Engage!

1284
01:53:46,627 --> 01:53:48,185
Break.

1285
01:54:03,143 --> 01:54:04,770
Penalty.

1286
01:54:19,126 --> 01:54:22,357
ANNOUNCER:
New Zealand, 12, South Africa, 9.

1287
01:54:22,529 --> 01:54:24,554
A great kick from Andrew Mehrtens.

1288
01:54:24,731 --> 01:54:27,791
Well, he certainly had length in reserve...

1289
01:54:27,968 --> 01:54:31,028
... because it was high, high
above the crossbar...

1290
01:54:44,852 --> 01:54:46,149
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1291
01:54:46,320 --> 01:54:48,652
REFEREE:
Penalty against green.

1292
01:54:51,992 --> 01:54:53,152
Time off.

1293
01:54:53,327 --> 01:54:55,852
- Five minutes, sir.
- Frangois.

1294
01:54:57,531 --> 01:55:00,125
Too many guys off their feet at the rucks.

1295
01:55:00,300 --> 01:55:02,097
- Okay.
- Speak to your team.

1296
01:55:02,269 --> 01:55:03,930
- I'll talk to them. Speak to them.
- Yes.

1297
01:55:04,104 --> 01:55:05,230
[CROWD SINGING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

1298
01:55:05,405 --> 01:55:06,667
ANNOUNCER:
Switch to Jonah Lomu.

1299
01:55:06,840 --> 01:55:10,276
Big man's been quiet in this match
and that's credit to South Africa's...

1300
01:55:10,677 --> 01:55:12,201
Heads up.

1301
01:55:12,379 --> 01:55:14,404
Look in my eyes.

1302
01:55:14,915 --> 01:55:16,507
Do you hear?

1303
01:55:16,683 --> 01:55:18,708
Listen to your country.

1304
01:55:18,886 --> 01:55:20,410
Seven minutes.

1305
01:55:20,721 --> 01:55:23,690
Seven minutes.
Defense, defense, defense.

1306
01:55:24,057 --> 01:55:25,490
This is it.

1307
01:55:25,659 --> 01:55:27,456
This is our destiny.

1308
01:55:27,628 --> 01:55:29,425
- Come, Bokke! Come!
- Yeah!

1309
01:55:29,596 --> 01:55:31,223
Come on!

1310
01:55:34,635 --> 01:55:36,762
How long before the end?

1311
01:55:36,937 --> 01:55:39,701
- Seven minutes.
- Seven minutes.

1312
01:55:39,873 --> 01:55:42,171
New Zealand leads by 12 points to 9.

1313
01:55:42,342 --> 01:55:45,311
This will be the longest seven minutes
that those 15...

1314
01:56:06,667 --> 01:56:08,931
Spin, spin!

1315
01:56:20,314 --> 01:56:22,748
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

1316
01:56:26,186 --> 01:56:30,179
Yes! Yes, Bokke!

1317
01:56:30,357 --> 01:56:34,191
Stransky, this time, has got this kick
of immense importance for his country.

1318
01:56:44,171 --> 01:56:45,536
Yeah.

1319
01:56:54,548 --> 01:56:56,709
ANNOUNCER:
Five minutes in extra playing time.

1320
01:57:03,090 --> 01:57:04,887
MAN:
Now, now!

1321
01:57:45,799 --> 01:57:48,290
And that is the way
one can get a big man coming...

1322
01:57:56,943 --> 01:57:58,501
Joost!

1323
01:58:12,459 --> 01:58:13,483
MAN:
And squeeze.

1324
01:58:20,334 --> 01:58:22,461
Joost!

1325
01:58:49,696 --> 01:58:50,720
Has he got it?

1326
01:58:54,267 --> 01:58:55,666
[CROWD CHEERING]

1327
01:58:56,937 --> 01:58:58,768
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1328
01:59:00,307 --> 01:59:06,405
ANNOUNCER: With minutes remaining,
South Africa takes the lead, 15 to 12.

1329
01:59:06,580 --> 01:59:07,740
Yes!

1330
01:59:15,889 --> 01:59:17,720
Fifteen points to 12.

1331
01:59:17,891 --> 01:59:19,722
South Africa!

1332
01:59:21,862 --> 01:59:23,693
[CHUCKLES]

1333
01:59:23,864 --> 01:59:26,594
[CROWD SINGING]

1334
01:59:34,608 --> 01:59:35,870
Ellis on the outside.

1335
01:59:36,076 --> 01:59:40,012
Great play here by Marc Ellis
in reading the game, but he can't take...

1336
01:59:41,615 --> 01:59:44,083
South Africa will have go into the scrum...

1337
01:59:54,694 --> 01:59:56,286
MAN:
Drive!

1338
02:00:28,061 --> 02:00:30,393
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

1339
02:00:49,483 --> 02:00:52,213
[WHISTLE BLOWING]

1340
02:00:55,989 --> 02:00:57,422
They've won!

1341
02:00:57,591 --> 02:00:59,855
- Yes!
- Yeah!

1342
02:01:07,300 --> 02:01:09,495
Yes!

1343
02:01:55,982 --> 02:01:58,416
Chester, will you lead us in a prayer?

1344
02:01:59,152 --> 02:02:01,677
Thanks, Lord,
for getting us into this final.

1345
02:02:01,855 --> 02:02:03,880
Thanks for no serious injuries.

1346
02:02:04,057 --> 02:02:07,083
And most of all,
thanks for the win. Amen.

1347
02:02:07,260 --> 02:02:08,887
Amen.

1348
02:02:16,803 --> 02:02:18,430
Good game.

1349
02:02:19,506 --> 02:02:21,667
Marvelous. Marvelous.

1350
02:02:21,841 --> 02:02:24,901
[CROWD SINGING "OLE OLE OLE"]

1351
02:02:25,579 --> 02:02:27,103
Good job.

1352
02:02:52,172 --> 02:02:56,108
[SINGING INDISTINCTLY]

1353
02:03:43,223 --> 02:03:46,386
Frangois, a few words.

1354
02:03:46,726 --> 02:03:47,852
Great game.

1355
02:03:48,028 --> 02:03:50,792
But you couldn't have done it
without the amazing support...

1356
02:03:50,964 --> 02:03:54,229
...of 63,000 South Africans here today.

1357
02:03:54,401 --> 02:03:57,996
Yeah. We didn't have the support
of 60,000 South Africans.

1358
02:03:58,171 --> 02:04:01,334
We had the support
of 43 million South Africans.

1359
02:04:01,508 --> 02:04:04,033
[CHEERING]

1360
02:04:16,723 --> 02:04:19,658
I want to thank you
for what you have done for our country.

1361
02:04:20,226 --> 02:04:23,957
No, Mr. President, thank you
for what you have done for our country.

1362
02:05:42,475 --> 02:05:45,376
Yeah, it's beautiful, it's beautiful,
it's beautiful.

1363
02:05:59,325 --> 02:06:02,351
This route is crowded.
Let's change to route C.

1364
02:06:02,529 --> 02:06:03,553
Okay.

1365
02:06:05,732 --> 02:06:10,260
There's no hurry here. No hurry at all.

1366
02:06:11,871 --> 02:06:14,806
LINGA:
Madiba says there's no need to hurry.

1367
02:06:17,010 --> 02:06:18,409
Yeah.

1368
02:06:21,181 --> 02:06:24,309
It's good, it's good, it's good.

1369
02:06:25,251 --> 02:06:28,516
MANDELA:
I thank whatever gods may be

1370
02:06:28,755 --> 02:06:31,815
For my unconquerable soul.

1371
02:06:31,991 --> 02:06:34,960
I am the master of my fate:

1372
02:06:35,261 --> 02:06:38,196
I am the captain of my soul.

1373
02:13:31,143 --> 02:13:33,134
[ENGLISH SDH]

